<SECOND>AM-Wickes Buyout,0464</SECOND>
<HEAD>Wickes `White Knight' Sigoloff Makes Leveraged Buyout Offer</HEAD>
<DATELINE>SANTA MONICA, Calif. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 <PERSON> Sanford </PERSON> <PERSON> C. </PERSON> <PERSON> Sigoloff </PERSON>, the corporate `` White Knight'' who rescued <ORGANIZATION> Wickes </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Cos. </ORGANIZATION>. Inc. from bankruptcy five years ago, on Sunday announced a management-led leveraged buyout offer of $ 12 a share The retail giant, including the Builder's Emporium and <ORGANIZATION> Wickes </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Furniture </ORGANIZATION> stores, also announced a net loss of $ 12.4 million for the second quarter ended July 30, said company spokesman <PERSON> Michael </PERSON> <PERSON> Sitrick </PERSON>. <PERSON> Sigoloff </PERSON> disclosed that <ORGANIZATION> WII </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Holdings </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Corp. </ORGANIZATION>, a firm he established with members of his <ORGANIZATION> Wickes </ORGANIZATION> management team, will offer to purchase nearly 40 million shares of outstanding common stock, <PERSON> Sitrick </PERSON> said. He said WII stands for W-2 or <ORGANIZATION> Wickes </ORGANIZATION> 2. The offer is nearly $ 3 higher than <ORGANIZATION> Wickes </ORGANIZATION>' closing stock price of 9 -RRB- on the <ORGANIZATION> New </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> York </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Stock </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Exchange </ORGANIZATION> last Friday. `` While I have strong confidence in the long-term viability and prospects of our continuing businesses,'' <PERSON> Sigoloff </PERSON> said in a prepared statement, `` it has become increasingly clear to me, as well as the other directors of the company, that our stockholders want to maximize the value of their investment in the company in the immediate near-term.'' The 39,846,600 shares sought in the merger deal represent about 83 percent of <ORGANIZATION> Wickes </ORGANIZATION>' outstanding shares, <PERSON> Sitrick </PERSON> said. The offer is scheduled to be in effect from Aug. 26 to Oct. 20, he said. It is expected that the principal investors in <ORGANIZATION> WII </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Holdings </ORGANIZATION> will be institutional investors, including <ORGANIZATION> Drexel </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Burnham </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Lambert </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Inc. </ORGANIZATION>, which promised no problems in arranging financing for the buyout, <PERSON> Sitrick </PERSON> said. The offer is void if fewer than 50 percent of outstanding shares are sold, he said. The company's net loss for the second quarter amounted to 28 cents a share, with reported earnings of $ 10.4 million, or 19 cents a share, on sales of $ 937.9 million and losses from discontinued operation of $ 22.8 million, or 47 cents a share. In April 1982, <ORGANIZATION> Wickes </ORGANIZATION>, with assets estimated at about $ 3 billion, became the largest <LOCATION> U.S. </LOCATION> company to file for bankruptcy protection. But less than two years later, creditors approved a plan allowing <ORGANIZATION> Wickes </ORGANIZATION> to emerge from Chapter 11 proceedings. Analysts had predicted it would take <ORGANIZATION> Wickes </ORGANIZATION> at least five years to erase the accumulated red ink. The force behind the comeback was <PERSON> Sigoloff </PERSON>, who earned the nickname `` Ming the Merciless'' for the tough-minded business moves and hard-nosed cost cutting he employed to resuscitate two other <LOCATION> Los </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Angeles </LOCATION> companies in the 1970s: <ORGANIZATION> Republic </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Corp. </ORGANIZATION> and <ORGANIZATION> Daylin </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Inc. </ORGANIZATION>. <PERSON> Sigoloff </PERSON> reorganized <ORGANIZATION> Wickes </ORGANIZATION> by selling off seasonal divisions such as <ORGANIZATION> MacGregor </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Golf </ORGANIZATION> and <ORGANIZATION> Wickes </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Agriculture </ORGANIZATION> At the same time he revamped store displays and appeared in television commercials and offered his personal guarantee of renewed product quality and service.
