<HEAD>Bust Nets 5,000 Pounds of Cocaine</HEAD>
<BYLINE>By RONALD POWERS</BYLINE>
<BYLINE>Associated Press Writer</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 Agents seized about 5,000 pounds of pure cocaine and $ 2 million in cash, including some stashed in bags marked `` Just Say No,'' authorities said in announcing one of the nation's largest drug confiscations Four people were arrested, including the local leader of a Colombian drug cartel, authorities said Sunday. The cocaine, with an estimated street value of $ 400 million, was the largest amount confiscated in <LOCATION> New </LOCATION> <LOCATION> York </LOCATION> <LOCATION> City </LOCATION>, said <PERSON> Robert </PERSON> <PERSON> M. </PERSON> <PERSON> Stutman </PERSON>, special agent in charge of the <ORGANIZATION> federal </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Drug </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Enforcement </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Administration </ORGANIZATION>'s office here. The largest cocaine shipment ever seized in the <LOCATION> United </LOCATION> <LOCATION> States </LOCATION>, in <LOCATION> Tampa </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> Fla. </LOCATION>, on April 28, involved 9,230 pounds found in plastic containers that were concealed in hallowed-out lumber. The largest in the <LOCATION> New </LOCATION> <LOCATION> York </LOCATION> <LOCATION> City </LOCATION> area occurred last month in <LOCATION> Hicksville </LOCATION>, where agents discovered 6,000 pounds of cocaine hidden inside blocks of chocolate from <LOCATION> Ecuador </LOCATION>. Only a few cocaine seizures nationally have exceeded 5,000 pounds. But Customs Service agents in 10 months have seized 10 tons more cocaine than they did in all of the last fiscal year, Customs Commissioner <PERSON> William </PERSON> <PERSON> von </PERSON> <PERSON> Raab </PERSON> said earlier this month. Among those arrested this weekend was <PERSON> Hernando </PERSON> <PERSON> Grajales </PERSON> <PERSON> Rizzo </PERSON>, 39, <LOCATION> Colombia </LOCATION>, a leader in the <LOCATION> Cali </LOCATION> drug cartel, <PERSON> Stutman </PERSON> said. <PERSON> Stutman </PERSON> would not say when or how the smugglers brought the drugs into <LOC