<HEAD>Results of Olympic Poll</HEAD>
<HEAD>With AM-Poll-Olympics Bjt</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 This <ORGANIZATION> Media </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> General-Associated </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Press </ORGANIZATION> poll is based on telephone interviews June 22-July 2 with 1,223 adults in the continental <LOCATION> United </LOCATION> <LOCATION> States </LOCATION>. The phone numbers were selected randomly by computer and interviews were conducted with the adult who had the most recent birthday. The results were weighted to adjust for variations in the sample. The poll has a three-point margin of error, meaning that if every adult American were asked the same questions, the results theoretically would be within three points of the poll's results, 19 times out of 20. There are other sources of potential error in polls, including the wording and order of questions. These are the questions and responses in this poll; because of rounding, some totals may exceed 100: 1. Do you think the Olympic Games should be held at one permanent site or should they continue to be held at a different location every four years? One site: 11 percent. Different: 85 percent. Do n't know-no answer: 4 percent. 2. Do you think the <LOCATION> United </LOCATION> <LOCATION> States </LOCATION> government should provide money to train <LOCATION> U.S. </LOCATION> Olympic athletes, or not? Yes: 67 percent. No: 27 percent. Do n't know-no answer: 6 percent. 3. Do you think professional athletes should be permitted to compete in all Olympic sports, some Olympic sports, or no Olympic sports: All: 35 percent. Some: 16 percent. None: 42 percent. Does n't Matter: 2 percent Do n't know-no answer: 5 percent. 4. Do you plan to watch some of the Olympic Games on television or not? Yes: 92 percent. No: 6 percent. Do n't know-no answer: 2 percent. 5. Do you think the Olympics encourage international cooperation, discourage international cooperation, or have no effect on it? Encourage: 76 percent. Discourage: 2 percent. No effect: 17 percent. Do n't know-no answer: 5 percent. 6. At the Summer Olympics, how important is it to you that the <LOCATION> United </LOCATION> <LOCATION> States </LOCATION> Olympic team wins more medals than any other nation's team Is it of: Great importance: 21 percent. Some importance: 41 percent. Little importance: 22 percent. No importance: 14 percent. Do n't know-no answer: 2 percent 7. How important is it to you that the <LOCATION> United </LOCATION> <LOCATION> States </LOCATION> Olympic team wins more medals than the Soviet team? Is it of: Great importance: 25 percent. Some importance: 34 percent. Little importance: 21 percent. No importance: 18 percent. Do n't know-no answer: 3 percent 8. In the sports that require judging, such as gymnastics, do you think the competitors are fairly judged, or not? Yes, 61 percent. No: 26 percent. Do n't know-no answer: 4 percent. 8a. -LRB- If no -RRB- Do you think the judges are influenced by political considerations, or not? Yes: 90 percent. No: 7 percent. Do n't know-no answer: 4 percent. 9. Do you think the Olympic Games have become too commercialized, or not? Yes: 50 percent. No: 46 percent. Do n't know-no answer: 5 percent.
