<HEAD>At the Movies: ``Moon Over Parador''</HEAD>
<BYLINE>By BOB THOMAS</BYLINE>
<BYLINE>Associated Press Writer</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
 In `` Moon Over Parador,'' <PERSON> Paul </PERSON> <PERSON> Mazursky </PERSON> reworks `` The Prince and the Pauper'' theme, adds outrageous farce and produces a marvelously comic view of Latin American politics and the acting profession. <PERSON> Mazursky </PERSON>'s earlier career was marked by relationship comedy-dramas, beginning with `` Bob & amp; <ORGANIZATION> Carol </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> & </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> amp </ORGANIZATION><ORGANIZATION> ; </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Ted </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> & </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> amp </ORGANIZATION>; <PERSON> Alice </PERSON>'' and continuing through `` Next Stop, <LOCATION> Greenwich </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Village </LOCATION>,'' `` An Unmarried Woman'' and `` <PERSON> Willie </PERSON> and <PERSON> Phil </PERSON>.'' With `` Down and Out in <LOCATION> Beverly </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Hills </LOCATION>,'' he broke through with a full-throttle comedy. `` Moon Over Parador'' could repeat that success. <PERSON> Richard </PERSON> <PERSON> Dreyfuss </PERSON> is a <LOCATION> New </LOCATION> <LOCATION> York </LOCATION> actor constantly on the prowl for that one star-making role. While he is playing a supporting role in a movie being shot on the <LOCATION> Caribbean </LOCATION> island of <LOCATION> Parador </LOCATION>, he meets the dictator-president and does an imitation of him. When the gourmand dictator dies of a heart attack during a carnival, the chief of police and power behind the throne, <PERSON> Raul </PERSON> <PERSON> Julia </PERSON>, uncorks a daring idea: <PERSON> Dreyfuss </PERSON> could impersonate the late ruler and thus prevent a revolution. Under threat of death, the actor accepts the role. <PERSON> Dreyfuss </PERSON> leaps into the impersonation, performing a brilliant balcony speech before the populace. But of course he ca n't deceive his servants, who decide to go along with the scheme. Nor can he fool his mistress, <PERSON> Sonia </PERSON> <PERSON> Braga </PERSON>, who also agrees to keep his secret. <PERSON> Julia </PERSON> and his cohorts, who appear to be left over from old <ORGANIZATION> Nazi </ORGANIZATION> movies, grow restless as <PERSON> Dreyfuss </PERSON> begins to propose liberal reforms. The natives are restless, too, and <PERSON> Dreyfuss </PERSON> is nearly killed by bombs. How he escapes from his predicament is an ingenious piece of scripting by <PERSON> Mazursky </PERSON> and <PERSON> Leon </PERSON> <PERSON> Capetanos </PERSON>. The success of `` Moon Over Parador'' is due in large part to ideal casting. <PERSON> Dreyfuss </PERSON> brilliantly portrays the insecurities of a struggling actor, and he proves a masterful farceur. <PERSON> Julia </PERSON>, in a Prussian wig, is the embodiment of slick evil, and <PERSON> Braga </PERSON> is both funny and sexy. <PERSON> Mazursky </PERSON> highlights the comedy with real-life cameo appearances. <PERSON> Sammy </PERSON> <PERSON> Davis </PERSON> <PERSON> Jr. </PERSON> sings for the carnival, <PERSON> Ike </PERSON> <PERSON> Pappas </PERSON> plays a television reporter. <PERSON> Ed </PERSON> <PERSON> Asner </PERSON> kids himself by paying a friendly visit to rebel camps in the mountains. The only disappointment is the usually reliable <PERSON> Jonathan </PERSON> <PERSON> Winters </PERSON>. His CIA agent is written on the one-note venality that has become a movie cliche. `` Moon Over Parador'' is rated PG-13, for bedroom scenes and language. Running time: 104 minutes.
