<HEAD>Stocks Broadly Lower, Dow Industrials At Nearly Three-Month Low</HEAD>
<NOTE>Eds: Updates with closing prices throughout. CORRECTS Amex change
in last graf to decline of 2.02 sted 2.002.</NOTE>
<BYLINE>By SKIP WOLLENBERG</BYLINE>
<BYLINE>AP Business Writer</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 Interest-rate worries drove the stock market broadly lower on Monday, pushing the closing Dow Jones Industrial Average below 2,000 for the first time in nearly three months. `` This is very nervous trading,'' said <PERSON> Jack </PERSON> <PERSON> Baker </PERSON>, head of block trading at <ORGANIZATION> Shearson </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Lehman </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Hutton </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Inc. </ORGANIZATION> `` This is n't the kind of market that's going to bring people off the sidelines.'' The Dow Jones average of 30 industrials, which lost 21.52 points last week, gave up another 25.78 to close at 1,990.22. That was the lowest closing level for the market's best-known indicator since it finished at 1,956.44 on May 27, the day before the three-day Memorial Day holiday. When traders returned May 31, the Dow climbed 74.68 points and the industrial average finished above 2,000 every day since then. Declining issues outpaced gainers by a margin of nearly 3 to 1 among issues listed on the <ORGANIZATION> New </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> York </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Stock </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Exchange </ORGANIZATION>, with 385 up, 1,107 down and 466 unchanged. The <ORGANIZATION> NYSE </ORGANIZATION> index fell 1.60 to 145.94. The pace of trading was sluggish, however. Volume on the floor of the <ORGANIZATION> NYSE </ORGANIZATION> amounted to 122.25 million shares, down from 122.37 million shares on Friday. Nationwide, consolidated volume in NYSE-listed issues, including trading at regional exchanges and on the over-the-counter market, totaled 144.90 million shares. As the market opened, stock prices pushed marginally higher, but quickly reversed course when a decline in bond prices drove fixed-income yields higher. Analysts said the yields available in the bond and money markets are keeping many investors out of the stock market. That inclination was even more pronounced on the eve of the first of a flurry of economic reports due to be released this week, analysts said. The government plans to report Tuesday on consumer prices for July. Later in the week, it planned to revise its estimate of second-quarter economic growth, among other things. The economy has been growing at such a strong pace that the <ORGANIZATION> Federal </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Reserve </ORGANIZATION> boosted its rate on loans to member banks by a half percentage point to 6.5 percent earlier this month in a bid to head off inflation. <ORGANIZATION> Shearson </ORGANIZATION>'s <PERSON> Baker </PERSON> said traders were worried that Tuesday's consumer price report would show a big jump that would encourage the central bank to push rates even higher That would make <ORGANIZATION> Treasury </ORGANIZATION> issues even more attractive to big institutional investors compared with the uncertain returns on stocks. On Monday, prices of the widely-followed 30-year <ORGANIZATION> Treasury </ORGANIZATION> bond fell $ 5 for every $ 1,000 in face value, pushing its yield to 9.45 percent from 9.39 percent on Friday. <PERSON> Alfred </PERSON> <PERSON> E. </PERSON> <PERSON> Goldman </PERSON>, director of technical market analysis for the brokerage <ORGANIZATION> A.G. </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Edwards </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> & </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> amp </ORGANIZATION><ORGANIZATION> ; </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Sons </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Inc. </ORGANIZATION> in <LOCATION> St. </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Louis </LOCATION>, said yields on shorter term issues are also attractive. He noted that 5-year Treasury issues are yielding about 9 percent, for instance, while the Dow Jones industrials have lost more than 160 points since early July. `` As long as stocks are going down, these will provide some very stiff competition for the investors dollar ... The institutional investor who has substantial cash reserves is saying, ` Why bother? I'll take a safe haven until the economic uncertainties clarify themselves','' <PERSON> Goldman </PERSON> said. <ORGANIZATION> Wickes </ORGANIZATION> was among the most actively-traded issues on the <ORGANIZATION> NYSE </ORGANIZATION>, jumping 3 ~ to 13 A management-led group proposed Sunday to take the company private in a leveraged buyout at $ 12 a share in cash and stock. There was also some interest in utility stocks that have either recently passed or are approaching deadlines for investors to qualify for dividends. <ORGANIZATION> Philadelphia </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Electric </ORGANIZATION> was the most active issue, down -LRB- at 17 -RCB-, while <ORGANIZATION> Kansas </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> City </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Power </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> & </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> amp </ORGANIZATION>; Light rose \ to 29 ~ Among actively traded blue chips, <ORGANIZATION> American </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Telephone </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> & </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> amp </ORGANIZATION>; <ORGANIZATION> Telegraph </ORGANIZATION> fell -LCB- to 24 \, <ORGANIZATION> Ford </ORGANIZATION> tumbled 1 -RCB- to 46 ~ and <ORGANIZATION> International </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Business </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Machines </ORGANIZATION> fell 2 to 110 Several airline stocks fell. AMR, the parent of <ORGANIZATION> American </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Airlines </ORGANIZATION>, was off 1 at 42 \, and <ORGANIZATION> UAL </ORGANIZATION>, parent of <ORGANIZATION> United </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Airlines </ORGANIZATION>, fell 2 | to The Wilshire Associates Equity Index, the market value of <ORGANIZATION> NYSE </ORGANIZATION>, American and OTC issues, fell $ 26.896 billion, or 1.03 percent, to $ 2.576 trillion. <ORGANIZATION> Standard </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> & </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> amp </ORGANIZATION>; Poor's industrial index fell 3.95 to 294.49, and <ORGANIZATION> S </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> & </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> amp </ORGANIZATION>; P's 500-stock composite 